title: Frieze, 1900–15
inscribed: Printed in selvedge: "Pittsburg W. P. Co. New Brighton, PA 1652"
description:
Foliate medallions connected by treillage pattern of foliate scrolls. Top and bottom each have a band of small and medium sized circular motifs forming a chain. Background has black and blue moiret. Ground is dark red. Printed in reds, pinks, blues, black, white mica, and yellows. 
Printed in selvedge: "Pittsburg W. P. Co. New Brighton, PA 1652"

tombstone.epitaph:
Frieze, 1900–15.
1900–15. Machine printed on paper. Gift of Victorian Collectibles. 1979-91-604.
